  return <MDXLayout {...layoutProps} {...props} components={components} mdxType="MDXLayout">


    <p><Highlight color="#1877F2" mdxType="Highlight">Beta</Highlight></p>
    <p>{`Sauce Labs Testrunner Toolkit is a containerized testing solution that simplifies user setup, speeds up test execution time and supports native Javascript frameworks like Puppeteer and Playwright for running end-to-end web tests with Sauce Labs.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "how-testrunner-toolkit-works"
    }}>{`How Testrunner Toolkit Works`}</h2>
    <p>{`Native JavaScript testing is achieved through the combination of Sauce Labs, Jest, and the
JavaScript framework of your choice. In the current beta, the toolkit supports:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer"
        }}>{`Puppeteer`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/microsoft/playwright"
        }}>{`Playwright`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/DevExpress/testcafe"
        }}>{`TestCafe`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress"
        }}>{`Cypress`}</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`This approach gives you the power and expressiveness of different test frameworks with the dashboards, infrastructure, and analytics of `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://saucelabs.com/"
      }}>{`Sauce Labs`}</a>{`. `}</p>
    <p>{`The specific framework you want to use for testing should be based on the types of tests you
need to run and the environment where you run the tests. `}</p>
    <p>{`In this beta, you will be able to run tests in your existing CI pipeline and benefit from the low latency. `}</p>
    <p>{`When tests complete, the test assets (logs, test results, and test videos) are uploaded to your `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://app.saucelabs.com"
      }}>{`Sauce Labs account`}</a>{`. From Sauce Labs you can review, share, and analyze the test results just as you would with any other test framework executed on Sauce Labs.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "resources"
    }}>{`Resources`}</h2>
    <p>{`To learn more about the tools associated with this project please see the links below:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Jest: `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://jestjs.io/"
        }}>{`https://jestjs.io/`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The Google Puppeteer project: `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://developers.google.com/web/tools/puppeteer"
        }}>{`https://developers.google.com/web/tools/puppeteer`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The Microsoft Playwright project: `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/microsoft/playwright"
        }}>{`https://github.com/microsoft/playwright`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`TestCafe: `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/"
        }}>{`https://devexpress.github.io/testcafe/`}</a></li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`Cypress: `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress"
        }}>{`https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress`}</a></li>
    </ul>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

